Plan for Your Data Integration Project

Before you build your data integration solution, think about the use case you want to analyze and the data you need to get you there.

Define What You Want To Analyze and Why

Clarify the purpose of your analysis. What area of your business do you want to target? What specific improvements do you want to make in this area? Understand what you want to learn from your data.

Define the Data Elements Needed for Your Analysis

Identify the most relevant objects and fields. Design the dataset that supports the analysis you want to conduct.

Identify the Best Data Source for Each Data Element

For each element, determine its data source: a Salesforce object or an external data source. Investigate details about individual data elements.

Determine What Data You Need for Your Analysis

Do you need all rows of data or can you filter on a specific segment? Focus on a particular demographic or range of values.

Determine the Time Window for Your Data

How far back in time do you want to go for your analysis? Filter out any data that is outside your time range.

Commit to Continuous Improvement

As you test your data integration and review the results, discover ways to improve your outcomes. Reconsider previous assumptions or change data sources to adapt to changes quickly.
title: Plan Your Data Integration Project
